Ted Odogwu, Kano The Independent National Electoral Commission has exempted members of the National Youth Service Corps from participating in the January 25 rerun in the Kiru and Bebeji Constituency of Kano State due to security concerns. The Kano State Electoral Commissioner, Prof. Riskua Shehu, stated this on Tuesday while briefing journalists on the commission’s preparations towards the by-elections, which would be held in nine local government areas of the state. He said the exemption of the NYSC members was a proactive measure to prevent a possible reprisal, over the death of an eight-year old boy, who stumbled and later died, while been chased by a corps member. Shehu, who said that all arrangements had been put in place to ensure a hitch-free election, noted that sensitive materials had yet to arrive, 11 days to the elections He said, “A total of 3, 456, ad hoc staff will be recruited but no NYSC member will be posted to Bebeji to serve as ad hoc staff based on security advice for the rerun election.” Copyright PUNCH.
